            "number": 5180,
            "lemma": "\u03c4\u1f7b\u03c0\u03c4\u03c9",
            "xlit": "t\u00fdpt\u014d",
            "pronunciation": "toop'-to",
            "kjv_def": "beat, smite, strike, wound.",
            "pspeech": "V-PNA",
            "description": " to \"thump\", i.e. cudgel or pummel (properly, with a stick or bastinado), but in any case by repeated blows; thus differing from \u03c0\u03b1\u1f77\u03c9(pa\u00ed\u014d) and \u03c0\u03b1\u03c4\u1f71\u03c3\u03c3\u03c9(pat\u00e1ss\u014d), which denote a (usually single) blow with the hand or any instrument, or \u03c0\u03bb\u1f75\u03c3\u03c3\u03c9(pl\u1e17ss\u014d) with the fist (or a hammer), or \u1fe5\u03b1\u03c0\u1f77\u03b6\u03c9(rhap\u00edz\u014d) with the palm; as well as from \u03c4\u03c5\u03b3\u03c7\u1f71\u03bd\u03c9(tynch\u00e1n\u014d), an accidental collision); by implication, to punish; figuratively, to offend (the conscience)"
        },
